---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import SocialLinks from '../components/SocialLinks.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>I'm Sonneko.<img src="/fonts/icon.png" width="100" class="icon-image" alt="Sonneko's icon" /></h1>
			<SocialLinks />

			<p>
				Hello, I'm Sonneko, a high school student in Japan. I'm learning computer science and mathematics as a hobby, with a focus on both theory and practice.
			</p>

			<p>
				I was honored to receive 8th place at the Science Koshien 2025 (National Final) and the Gold Award at the "Rear Biz" High School Student Entrepreneurship Grand Prix. I am also the founder of <a href="https://aoristos.net">Aoristos</a>, an independent student-led self-study organization.
			</p>

			<p>
				My technical interests are broad, ranging from computer science and modern physics to analysis. I enjoy self-studying topics such as linear algebra, AI theory, compiler development, cognitive philosophy, programming language design, and decentralized applications (blockchain). I am often inspired by STEM YouTubers like 3Blue1Brown, Yobinori, and Lambda Tech, and I strive to combine theoretical learning with practical product development.
			</p>

			<h3>Recent Activities & OSS</h3>
			<p>
				I am active in the developer community and have contributed to OSS projects, such as developing the <a href="https://github.com/sonneko/mdbook-sitemap">mdbook-sitemap</a> backend. My primary languages are TypeScript and Rust, though I also use Python when appropriate. Currently, I am exploring Go, Zig, and Haskell.
			</p>

			<p>
				I primarily use GitHub Codespaces on an iPad with a physical keyboard for my development environment. I often host my projects on GitHub Pages or Cloudflare, and use Vercel for SSR requirements.
			</p>

			<h3>Projects</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><b>Hydent Lang</b>: A new programming language focused on safety and speed. <a href="https://github.com/sonneko/hydent-lang">Repo</a></li>
				<li><b>mdbook-sitemap</b>: A tool to generate sitemap.xml for mdBook. <a href="https://github.com/sonneko/mdbook-sitemap">Repo</a></li>
				<li><b>Air Keyboard</b>: A camera-based virtual keyboard using Google MediaPipe. <a href="https://github.com/sonneko/air-keyboard">Repo</a></li>
				<li><b>Investment Simulator</b>: LLM-powered investment simulation using GitHub Actions and Gemini. <a href="https://github.com/sonneko/investment-simulator">Repo</a></li>
				<li><b>Programming Book</b>: A comprehensive guide to CS and programming for beginners (in Japanese). <a href="https://github.com/sonneko/programming-book">Repo</a></li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Tech Stack</h3>
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Domain</th>
						<th>Technologies</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>Languages</td>
						<td>Rust, TypeScript, Python (Learning: Go, Zig, Haskell)</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Frontend</td>
						<td>Astro, Svelte, Next.js, Solid.js, Tailwind, Material Components</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Infrastructure</td>
						<td>Cloudflare, GitHub Pages, Vercel, GitHub Actions</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Others</td>
						<td>Compiler Design, WebRTC, LLM Integration (Gemini, Claude)</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>

			<h3>Contact</h3>
			<p>
				If you have any questions or would like to get in touch, please feel free to open an issue in <a href="https://github.com/sonneko/sonneko">this repository</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.icon-image {
		margin-left: 15px;
		vertical-align: middle;
	}
</style>
